      <p>Tomtom automatically detects the orientation but if for some reason the
      correct orientation isn't being detected it can be specified in the 
      advanced section.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_f_orient">
      <p>A matrix is column oriented if it has 4 rows and any number of columns.
      The original Tomtom web format was column oriented. A matrix is row 
      oriented if it has 4 columns and any number of rows.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_f_sites">
      <p>The site count is only used when a probability matrix is specified, 
      otherwise it is derived from the matrix.</p> 
      <p>The pseudocount is added to each residue in proportion to the 
      background. Thus the total count for a position is the site count plus 
      the pseudocount.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_motif_m">
      <p>By default only the first motif is searched but this can be changed in 
      the advanced section. To search with more than one motif Tomtom must 
      process your request as part of a queue and hence a contact email will be 
      required. See more information on the <a href="../doc/meme-format.html"
      >meme format</a> and the <a href="../examples/sample-dna-motif.meme-io"
      >sample</a> MEME DNA motifs.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_m_filter">
    <p>The filter supports selecting motifs from the file by their name and/or 
    their order in the file. Any numbers are assumed to refer to the position of
    the motif in the file. Any other entry is assumed to be a motif name (or 
    ID). Motif names can not start with a dash and can only contain 
    alphanumeric characters plus <b>:</b> <b>_</b> <b>.</b> and <b>-</b>. The 
    motifs should be separated by spaces.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_db_file">
      <p>An uploaded database is a normal <a href="../doc/meme-format.html"
      >MEME</a> DNA motif file with lots of motifs. The uploaded database must 
      be smaller than 5MB.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_email">
      <p>The email is used to notify you of your results but is not stored.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_job_description">
      <p>The job description will be included in the notification email you 
      receive.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" style="display:none" id="pop_comparison_function">
      <p>Motifs are compared column by column. In the following equations 
      <b><i>X</I></b> is the set of probabilities from one column and 
      <b><i>Y</i></b> the probabilities from the compared column. The subscript 
      <b><i>a</i></b> refers to the letter from the nucleotide alphabet 
      <b><i>A</i></b>.</p>
      <dl class="meanings">
        <dt>Pearson correlation coefficient</dt>
        <dd><img src="../images/pearson-eq.png" /></dd>
        <dt>Euclidean distance</dt>
        <dd><img src="../images/euclidean-eq.png" /></dd>
        <dt>Sandelin-Wasserman similarity</dt>
        <dd><img src="../images/sandelin-eq.png" /></dd>
      </dl>
      <div class="pop_close">[ 
        <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_thresh">
      <p>There are two ways of specifying the threshold.</p>
      <dl class="meanings">
        <dt><i>E-value</i></dt>
        <dd>The expected number of false positives. This may be any positive 
        number.</dd>
        <dt><i>q-value</i></dt>
        <dd>Minimum <b>F</b>alse <b>D</b>iscovery <b>R</b>ate at which a result 
        is declared significant. This is a number between zero and one 
        non-inclusive.</dd>
      </dl>
      <div class="pop_close">[ 
        <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_complete_scoring">
      <p>Complete scoring takes into account unaligned columns in the 
      calculation of scores. It is recommended that you leave this feature 
      enabled unless you are trying to recreate old results.</p>
      <div class="pop_close">[ 
        <a href="javascript:help_popup()">close</a> ]</div>
    </div>

    <div class="pop_content" id="pop_f_bg">
